pagesData[53] = {
    author: "SM",
    text: `<p>That voice is a pure poison pouring right into the ears like on good old Shakespeare’s plays. But for some twisted, sick reason this poison is healing same time with killing; hell know how that works but Sebastian clinges to these sounds like a drowning man grabbing a lifeline. The voice, the warmth of the hot body so close, the familiar feeling of a head placed onto his shoulder—how many times would JM doze off like this?—and his cruel words.</p>
<p>Moran would never admit he’s right. He deceives himself telling it’s not the words he needs but just the sound to fill the emptiness in the world around him, just because he got too used to this sounds. And that’s a sweet lie; he does really enjoy those fucking orders, that bloody condescending tone, that humiliating mockery intertwined with strangely careful possessiveness. As if JM understands his toy is very, very expensive and almost unique, and tries to keep it safe and sound while playing hard. It’s all too complex to be packed in words and meanings, actually.</p>
