pagesData[55] = {
    author: "SM",
    text: `<p>Still being blindfolded, Moran senses everything vividly—the sounds, the feelings, the warmth. The embrace feels strangely comfortable, no matter they lead to lie down on the absolutely not soft and not warm floor. Then the familiar weight comes over, covering him like a heavy blanket, and the specific sense of a tongue touching his face.
Moran says nothing, mostly because he just can’t catch his breath; and also because he absolutely doesn’t know what shall he say.</p>
<p>Slowly the heartbeat becomes slower and more steady, and it feels like the temperature in the room is down. Moran finds himself embracing JM carefully like he did so many times before, listening to his breath and feeling his heartbeat, usually much quicker than own.
Then this familiar weight and sensation is gone, as soon as JM decided to either get up or just move aside. Though the sounds tell he’s looking for the bathrobe and then moves back again just to burn with a whisper and finally go away.</p>
