pagesData[56] = {
    author: "JM",
    text: `<p>JM lies immovable across the covers of the king-size bed, his eyes closed and mouth open, and it's not until he feels the edge of the bed sag under the weight of another when he decides to finally crawl under the blanket and leave some space for Sebastian. The bathrobe flies to hang on the nearest chair. It might be pretty mean of him to bring chaos to Moran's usually neat place, but JM wants to make himself comfortable and it feels like the most important thing right now, and he knows Sebastian will take care of the rest because he's the man who doesn't need to be told anything twice. Actually, he doesn't even need to be told once, because he knows the deal, the thing with security, the thing with priority; and it's the best fucking feeling to just let him work everything out, knowing for sure he'll do it right.</p>
<p>And by the way, it's cute that he never removed the second pillow and the second toothbrush and many of such "second"s, obviously, hoping that JM might come back.</p>
<p>Once they both are under the blanket, JM snuggles up to Moran and rubs his face against the bare skin of his chest like an affectionate cat, showing that he's content. Sebastian might as well be covered in catnip because JM is pressing up against him like it's addictive, or maybe it's just the warmth of his body helping him to get even more comfy, anyway, it feels Good. JM remembers how alienated and confronting he appeared earlier, the "When are you going to dump me?", the wrist-grabbing and face-punching (JM actually had to press ice to his bruise the night after their fight in the coffeeshop); and now he's letting him stay in the same bed, cling to him, nuzzle, snuggle, nibble and do pretty much everything, remaining unbothered like a tiger who keeps resting next to a playful cub fooling around. Such permissiveness is making JM horny again.</p>
<p>But he's sooo tired, and he curls up a little and is almost ready to fall asleep, with his lips still pressed to Sebastian's collarbone and suckling on it inertly. And then he is reminded that he hasn't answered the question yet. The big question.</p>
<p>He becomes still and stops breathing for a moment, then stares up at Sebastian, his eyes looking like two holes falling into the head. And it's impossible to read them at first, whether it's anger in them, or surprise, or anything at all. But there's actually something way weirder.</p>
<p>He knows he can just drop it. He decides whether he wants to share this.</p>
<p>"Do you think there are things that are supposed to stay unknown?" JM pronounces, choosing words carefully, while his heartbeat accelerates. "I mean, would you believe me if I told you I'm not... sure... about things?"</p>`
